m/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  undecided</span><hr size=1> OK guys, I have to come clean.  I hate those people who on surveys respond UNDECIDED or NO OPINION.<br>
And as you all can tell, I am not shy about sharing my own opinions <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
BUT on this issue, I just don't have any idea what I think.  I know drugs destroy lives.  But so does alcohol.  I also buy the idea that the criminal aspect would decrease (not go away altogether) if they were legalized.  But I just find it absurd that we could legalize something so addictive and lethal.  Hmmmmm so here I sit on the fence. -- Shirene <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pagels@religiousdebate60574>Pagels</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#3333ff>(1/23/03 1:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Crime, money and drugs. </span><hr size=1> I find the War on Drugs to be very mixed up in how our society views race,poverty, and morality.<br>
<br>
People who work hard and get ahead are moral. <br>
People who work hard don't do drugs. People who work hard don't live by drug dealers.<br>
<br>
Ergo...<br>
<br>
Poor people aren't working hard enough if they are still poor. <br>
Therefore, they have no morals. People without morals do drugs. <br>
The reason poor people live in areas with dealers is because they want the drugs. <br>
So the problem with drug dealers is that the people who live where they deal just need to stop buying the drugs.<br>
<br>
<br>
